Egyptian Stocks: Alexandria Containers, Ascom, Citadel, Remco

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-06-05T10:26:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-05/egyptian-stocks-alexandria-containers-ascom-citadel-remco.html
Egypt ’s benchmark EGX 30 Index rose
1.3 percent to 5,432.62 as of 11:54 a.m. in Cairo, headed for
the biggest daily gain in a week.  The following shares rose or fell in Cairo. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Alexandria Containers & Goods (ALCN)   advanced as much as
2.7 percent before trading 0.6 percent higher at 94 Egyptian
pounds. The Egyptian container-handling company was raised to
“hold” from “sell” at CI Capital Holding with a 12-month
share-price estimate of 108.1 pounds.  Asec Co. for Mining (ASCM EY) rose 2.7 percent, the biggest
intraday gain since May 29, to 12.23 pounds. The unit of private
equity company Citadel Capital SAE said the board of directors
approved a plan to increase capital by 100 million pounds ($16.8
million) to 450 million pounds through a rights offering to
existing shareholders. Proceeds will be used to fund expansion,
the company known as Ascom said. Shares of Cairo-based Citadel
gained 2 percent to 6.07 pounds.  Remco for Touristic Villages Construction (RTVC)   dropped
4.1 percent to 3.05 pounds, the lowest intraday level since May
26. The resorts developer said it will not distribute a dividend
for 2010. The company paid shareholders a 10 percent stock
dividend last June, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
